            <thetext>It&apos;d be nice if at some point in the future we could rename all the cyrus
binaries to cyr_whatever (cyrwhatever?).  This will prevent conflicts with
binaries like master, deliver, imapd, pop3d, fetchnews, etc.

Certainly, going forward, we should try to name things cyrwhatever as we create
them.

The problem with doing this is that it will break effectively every deployed
configuration, so its something I&apos;m hesitant to do outside of a major version
number bump (but, by itself, it does not justify a major version).

Filing as low priority.</thetext>
